patients is comparable to other risks that health care workers have faced 
knowingly and have accepted in the recent past. However, the loss of 
quality-adjusted life expectancy associated with a needlestick exposure is 
significant. Identification of cost-effective methods that increase the safety 
of medical personnel but also ensure full access to high-quality care for HIV+ 
patients should be a high priority.

