There was no difference in the distribution of thromboses, elevated 
recirculations, or infections causing the first complication in patients with or 
without diabetes, but complications occurred earlier in diabetic patients (175 
+/- 26 v 286 +/- 36 days, P less than 0.01). Nondiabetic patients with 
prosthetic fistula complications were significantly older than those without 
complications (64 +/- 4 and 56 +/- 2 years, respectively, P less than 0.05). No 
impact of age on complications was found in diabetic patients. The probability 
of a first thrombosis at 6 and 12 months was 29% and 49% in nondiabetic and 55% 
and 72% in diabetic patients (P less than 0.05).(ABSTRACT TRUNCATED AT 250 
