The clinical performance of the TCu200B and TCu380A was evaluated by life table 
analysis in a cohort of women who wore an IUD from July 1979 to July 1982. This 
paper presents the results up to five years of use. No significant differences 
in age and parity were found between the users in the two groups. Overall 
performance was very good with both models. The cumulative continuation rate was 
